An Act relative to abandoned remains.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 1 of Chapter 38 of the Massachusetts General Laws shall be
2 amended by adding the following definition:
3 “Abandoned Remains”- The remains or a dead body that no one has taken legal authority
4 of the body for a period of 15 days.
5 SECTION 2. Chapter 38 of the Massachusetts General Laws shall be amended by
6 inserting after Section 16, the following new Section:
7 Section 17. Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, the office of the
8 chief medical officer shall accept for temporary storage abandoned remains, as defined in this
9 chapter, of persons who have died of natural causes in facilities licensed by the department of
10 public health under MGL Chapter 111 Section 71 or under MGL Chapter 111 Section 51 or other
